                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d267">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10–2847: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-10-28">October 28,
                            1947</date>.<lb/>[Received October 28—2:03 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2149. By official decree Democratic League has been declared an illegal
                    organization. Local authorities have been directed to suppress League activities
                    and to punish illegal activities of League members in accordance with measures
                    similar to those applied to Communists as stated in Government’s general
                    mobilization order promulgated on July 4, 1947.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
